The aim of the course is to handle problems related to human's performance capacity. The course is focused to specifity of different kind of physical activity and exercise training and to impact of the external environment on physical performance (response to heat and cold, impact of low atmospheric pressure). The course consists practical part focused to assessment and monitoring exercise training.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to handle problems related to human's performance capacity. Special attention will be paid to the specifity of performance capacity as well to the role of environmental conditions affecting performance. The course consists practical part related to assessment and monitoring the load of exercise.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Passing the course the student: 1) has knowledges about principles of exercise training; 2) has knowledges about improvement of performance capacity and factors related; 3) has knowledges about improvement of different kind of physical capacity; 4) has knowledges about the impact of external environment to performance capacity; 5) is able to build up the exercise plan; 6) is able during physical load to register and assess objective characteristics of subjects and on this basis guide exercise plan.
